## Installation 
 Do you want to make your cool code shorts public? 
 CodeMeme2Share is available as an [npm package](https://npmjs.com/package/codememe2share) 

 To install and save in your ```package.json``` dependencies, run: 

 ### npm 
 ``` 
 npm install codememe2share 
 ``` 
 ### yarn 
 ``` 
 yarn add codememe2share 
 ```

## Usage 
 Is time to code: 
 ### Quick start 
 Here's a quick example to get you started, it's literally all you need: 
 ``` 
 import React from "react"; 
 import ReactDom from "react-dom" 

 
 import MemeShare, { Container, AppleDots, Title } from "codememe2share" 

 const App () => { 
   return ( 
     <MemeShare> 
      <Container> 
	<AppleDots /> 
	<Title variant="h3"> 
	    Hola Mundo 
	</Title> 
      </Container> 
     </MemeShare> 
   ); 
 } 

 ReactDom.render(<App />, document.getElementById("root")); 
 ```
